The paper discusses the use of reinforcement learning for autonomous robots, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The focus is on the development of a world model to support adaptive behavior and learning, which is relevant to robotics (cs.RO) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also describes a computational model, which involves neural networks, that is used to formalize the hypothesis, which is relevant to neural networks (cs.NE) and computer vision (cs.CV).
